      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 24:5-9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The shewbread consisted of 12 unleavened cakes of fine meal, which were laid fresh every Sabbath in two rows of six upon the table in the Holy Place. Their preparation fell to the duty of the Kohathite Levites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 9:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The antiquity of this rite is shown by the story of David. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 21:2-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The name by which ‘the shewbread’ is here designated is ‘bread of arrangement,’ ‘lekhem hammaa-reketh’ (Vulg. ‘panes propositionis). The LXX. renders ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰς ἄρτους τοῦ προσώπου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘bread of the face,’ which is the translation of the other Hebrew name by which it was known, ‘lekhem happânîm:’ we should have expected ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰς ἄρτους προθέσεως",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the continual meat",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
